    "body": "Same for me, I had the following in my `starship.toml`:\n```\n[env_var.ARM_STAGE]\ndefault = ''\nstyle = \"bold yellow\"\nsymbol = '</>'\nformat = '[([$symbol](fg)$env_value)]($style)'\n\n[env_var.ARM_PROD]\ndefault = ''\nstyle = \"bold red\"\nsymbol = '</>'\nformat = '[([$symbol](fg)$env_value)]($style)'\n```\n\nAnd it produces the following prompt (this is the default, without both evironment variables being present):\n<img width=\"79\" height=\"73\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7a1716ff-89aa-4c5d-a9d4-113f8ebcfa5a\" />\n\n[My full config](https://github.com/yylian/dotfiles/blob/main/dotfiles/starship/starship.toml). I'm on fish and not zsh. Should my fish config be relevant, it is right next to the starship config. Like the OP I use kitty as terminal emulator.",
